
[1]truncheon

   TRUN'CHEON, n. [L. truncus.] A short staff; a club; a cudgel; a
   battoon; used by kings and great officers as a mark of command.

   The marshal's truncheon nor the judge's robe.

            TRUN'CHEON, v.t. To beat with a truncheon; to cudgel.
